<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17641212-18">
               <interp inst="t17641212-18" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17641212-18" type="year" value="1764"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17641212-18" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17641212"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17641212-18" type="date" value="17641212"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17641212-18-off88-c112" targOrder="Y" targets="t17641212-18-defend148 t17641212-18-off88 t17641212-18-verdict91"></join>
         
               <p>19. (M.) 
               <persName id="t17641212-18-defend148" type="defendantName">
                  August
               <interp inst="t17641212-18-defend148" type="given" value="August"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17641212-18-defend148" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             (a <rs id="t17641212-18-deflabel87" type="occupation">Negroman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17641212-18-defend148 t17641212-18-deflabel87"></join>) was indicted for <rs id="t17641212-18-off88" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17641212-18-off88" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17641212-18-off88" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing two guineas and a pair of scissars
            </rs>, the property of 
               
                  <persName id="t17641212-18-victim150" type="victimName">
                     Lionel 
                     Leonard 
                  <interp inst="t17641212-18-victim150" type="surname" value="Leonard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17641212-18-victim150" type="given" value="Lionel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17641212-18-victim150" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17641212-18-off88 t17641212-18-victim150"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17641212-18-cd89" type="crimeDate">November 22</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17641212-18-off88 t17641212-18-cd89"></join>. +</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17641212-18-person151">
                  Lionel 
                  Leonard 
               <interp inst="t17641212-18-person151" type="surname" value="Leonard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17641212-18-person151" type="given" value="Lionel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17641212-18-person151" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner is <rs id="t17641212-18-deflabel90" type="occupation">servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17641212-18-defend148 t17641212-18-deflabel90"></join> to a gentleman that has my first floor: I live in Duke-street, Lincoln's-Inn-Fields; I heard the prisoner own he had taken the two guineas mentioned in the indictment, and that he had bought some silver buckles with part of the money.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17641212-18-person152">
                  William 
                  Leonard 
               <interp inst="t17641212-18-person152" type="surname" value="Leonard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17641212-18-person152" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17641212-18-person152" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I laid two guineas (my brother's property) into a drawer in the bureau, in the parlour, on Wednesday the 21st of November; the drawer was not locked: the next day they<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="176412120009"></xptr> were missing; I suspected August, and took him before Justice Welch; there he owned he had taken them; but when he owned it, he was very much in liquor: he said, he had bought two pair of silver buckles with it; they were in his shoes and knees: he did not say what he had done with the rest of the money.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I saved that money up, by dressing people's hair, and finishing coffins.</p>
               <p>Prosecutor. I am a coffin-maker: I have frequently employed 
               <persName id="t17641212-18-person153">
                  August.
               <interp inst="t17641212-18-person153" type="given" value="August."></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17641212-18-person153" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             I have trusted him with things of hundreds of pounds value, and never missed any thing before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17641212-18-person154">
                  George 
                  Vaughan 
               <interp inst="t17641212-18-person154" type="surname" value="Vaughan"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17641212-18-person154" type="given" value="George"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17641212-18-person154" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I brought the prisoner from abroad; he has had it in his power to have robbed me of things of great Value: he has several times brought my purse to me: I never missed money out of it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17641212-18-person155">
                  John 
                  Clark 
               <interp inst="t17641212-18-person155" type="surname" value="Clark"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17641212-18-person155" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17641212-18-person155" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . (one of the jury.) The prisoner's master's sister lodged at my house a year and a half: he used to come to and fro' with messages, and has been in my house for hours together, and I never missed any thing by him.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17641212-18-verdict91" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17641212-18-verdict91" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               Acquitted
            </rs>.</p>
            </div1>
